<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="The GIS502TunerHMI.caldef file defines the calibrations to support user HMI settings primarily for tuner functionality.  This includes default menu settings and other UI specific settings used to tailor the HMI experience.  ">
  <CalDefFileVersion>12</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>20Feb2015</Date>
    <Description>&#xD;
&#xD;
GIS502TunerHMI.caldef change log for Feb 20 2015 release:&#xD;
&#xD;
1.  Deleted AM FM Fast Seek and AM FM Fast Tune as they are already defined in the GIS653AMFMTunerCommon.caldef file.&#xD;
&#xD;
2.  Changed DeviceFriendlyName default value from 2 secs to 3 seconds.&#xD;
&#xD;
3.  Deleted DAB_FastSeekTune as it is already defined in GIS-655DABTuner.caldef.&#xD;
&#xD;
4.  Changed limits of DirectTuneSXM_Message as they were not defined to match GIS-502.&#xD;
&#xD;
5.  Added the RDS_Radio_Menu_Item_On calibration to control the default setting for RDS information in the HMI.&#xD;
&#xD;
6.  Deleted HDRadio as it is not required.  Replaced with HD_Radio_Menu_Item_On to control the default setting for HD On/Off in the HMI.&#xD;
&#xD;
7.  Added the following new calibrations to set the HMI menu item state for various tuner functions:&#xD;
RDS_Radio_Menu_Item_On&#xD;
Album_Art_Menu_Item_On&#xD;
HD_Radio_Menu_Item_On&#xD;
Explicit_Content_Menu_Item_On&#xD;
MetadataCorrector_Menu_Item_On&#xD;
&#xD;
8.  Added SXM Source Mode cal as defined in GIS-502.&#xD;
&#xD;
9.  Added Set_Number_Display_Favorites as an enumerated value as defined in GIS-502.&#xD;
&#xD;
10. Added driver workload cals:  MediaBrowseLockout, StationChannelListLockout, and SlideShow_AlbumArt_LockOut as defined in GIS-502/GIS-500. &#xD;
&#xD;
11. Added Metadata_Paging_Rates as defined in GIS-502.&#xD;

12. Changed the description for the SplashScreen to apply only for 3rd party apps.&#xD;  

13. Added new cal called 3rdPartyAppLaunchTime to define a timer used to determine if the SplashScreen should be displayed.  When a 3rd party app is launched this cal establishes a timer that, if expires prior to the 3rd party app running, will trigger the display of the SplashScreen to provide a form of system feedback to the user.  This calibration is used in tandem with the SplashScreen calibration.&#xD;
</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>3/19/2015</Date>
    <Description>Changed name of the Cal 3rdPartyAppLaunchTime to ThirdPartyAppLaunchTime because the previous naming convention with this Cal starting with a number is an invalid cal name that the Java compliler doesn't accept.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>April 15, 2015</Date>
    <Description>The following changes were added to the April 15th release of calibrations.  &#xD;
1. Added cal parameters: Slideshow_DAB_Band_Image_Display_Time, SlideShowAlphaBlend, SlideShow_TransitionTime,SlideShow_TimeOut.

2. Added the Audio_Now_Playing_Layout cal to specify the Now Playing layout view for the North American and other markets.

3.  Added DAB_Station_Not_Available cal to provide a time-out for display of DAB metadata in the presence of DAB signal loss.

4. Reviewed and corrected the GIS-502 reference paragraphs shown for each calibration.

5. Added the Album_Art_Menu_Item_On calibration to specify in the menu the default state for displaying Album Art images.

6. Added the DAB_Announcement_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for DAB Announcements. 

7. Added the DAB_DAB_Linking_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for DAB to DAB Linking. 

8. Added the Traffic_Program_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for Traffic Program Announcements.  

9. Added the DAB_FM_Linking_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for DAB to FM Linking. 

10. Deleted the DirectTune calibration as it is not required for DAB direct tuning.

11. Added the Tune_Mix_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for SXM Tune Mix. 

12. Added the Tune_Start_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for SXM Tune Start. 

13. Added the Instant_Replay_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for SXM Instant Replay. 

14. Added the Sports_Flash_Menu_Item_On calibration to define the HMI menu item default state for SXM Sports Flash. 

15. Added the Traffic_Information_Menu_Item_on cal for the Japan Traffic Information.

16. Changed usage of MetadataCorrectorLogo to Mid/High only as it is not applicable for Low Radio.

17. Changed FavDely range to 500 to 2000 msec as an valid range was not originally defined.

18. Changed FavWidgetRemoval range to 2 to 6 seconds as a valid range was not originally defined.

19. Changed HUD Audio update range to 2 to 10 seconds as a valid range was not originally defined.

20. Changed name on MetadataCorrector to MetadataCorrector Menu Item On to be consistent with the other &quot;Menu_Item_On cals.

21.  Delete CategoriesByRegion as it is already defined in tuner cal def files. Also,per request from Sanghyun Ryu updated VideoLockOut, HDMulticast, ThirdPartyAppLaunchTime, Splashscreens, MetadataCorrectorLogo, HUDAudioUpdate, and MetadataCorrector cals in this caldef file to remove usage of Low Radio.
</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gross/Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>7/30/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per discussion with Al Budyta, deleted the Metadata_Corrector_Menu_Item_On CAL (CalID: _6MRh4GlNEeSUD4W2RgDvTg) from this CalDef file as it has a duplicate function to the MetadataCorrector_Menu_Item_On CAL (CalID: _LvV2oblIEeSMLcx9-dghJQ ) that already existed in this file. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file deleted the ToneSettingsDescription CAL, as it was confirmed in discussions with James Stefanovski, Cody Hansen, and Dominic Colella this CAL does not have any needed use for Info3.0. Also the DirectTuneLockout CAL was incorrectly defined as a Boolean type CAL initially in the GIS-502. This CAL should have been defined as Enumeration type CALs instead since this CAL is a driver work load CAL,, and needs to be assoissicated to the DriverWorkload.enumdef the same as how the other driver work load CALs are handled. In order to do this, deleting the DirectTuneLockout CAL(CalID: _sBLxoGlMEeSUD4W2RgDvTg) that was defined as a Boolean type CAL, and this previously existing CAL needs to be replaced by the newly added DirectTuneLockout CAL (CalID: _itkrkN4BEeW58O1OdVks4w) that is defined as an Enumeration type CAL. This update to define the DirectTuneLockout as an Enumeration type CALs instead of a Boolean type CALs are also reflected in the latest published GIS-502 Spec., version 3.3. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>2016-Jun-17</Date>
    <Description>Clean-up and clarification of cals as per CR 1096165. Added cals to match with GIS-502 for following parameters. HD_Radio_Multicast_Tuning,DAB_DisplayDABCategories,DAB_Slide_Show_Menu_Item_On,MetadataCorrector,CategoriesByRegion.Corrected description of DAB_Source_Mode.Revised SlideShow_Transition_Time as: units to Seconds from milliseconds,range to 5-20 seconds,  Revised default to 15 seconds. Deleted Tune_Mix_Menu_Item_On.Deleted Slideshow_Transition_Time because the DAB radio stream has built in time delay in audio stream.</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added two enumeration type calibrations (DAB_EPG_Length_EventDescriptionDetailedViewInDrivingMode and DAB_EPG_Length_EventDescriptionDetailedViewInParkingMode) shown as needed in the GIS-502 Audio UI starting for MY19.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>10/1/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS502_TunerHMI.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef, except for the following calibrations within this caldef file: 1.) HDMulticast, 2.) HD_Radio_Multicast_Tuning, 3.) HUDAudioUpdate, 4.) MetadataCorrector, 5.) MetadataCorrector_Menu_Item_On, Splashscreens, 6.) ThirdPartyAppLaunchTime, and 7.) VideoLockOut. Note, did not add GEM usage for these seven calibrations since these seven calibraions did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>6/20/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR# 2303176, create new calibration RDS_PTY_Radio_Menu_Item_On to meet RDS regulatory reqs. Per CR# 2303176, 2303157, 2303128, 2303019: AOSP transition in MY22 GIS-646 Cal DB V6.0.3, deprecating the following cals for AOSP transition and decontent: Explicit_Content_Menu_Item_On, DAB_EPG_LengthEventDescriptionDetailedViewInDrivingMode, DAB_EPG_LengthEventDescriptionDetailedViewInParkingMode, DAB_Slide_Show_Menu_Item_On, DeviceFriendlyName,  HD_Radio_Menu_Item_On, HD_Radio_Multicast_Tuning, HDMulticast, Instant_Replay_Menu_Item_On, Slideshow_AlbumArt_LockOut, SlideShow_Alpha_Blend, Slideshow_DAB_Band_Image_Display_Time, SlideShow_TimeOut, Sports_Flash_Menu_Item_On, and Tune_Start_Menu_Item_On. </Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
