  <CalDefinition Description="The DAB_Station_Not_Available calibration is a timer used to delay the display of the DAB Station Not Available message in cases where the DAB signal drops below an acceptable receive signal threshold in the tuner. While the timer is active (i.e., not expired) HMI shall continue to display the current metadata for the existing broadcast even if the signal is lost and audio is now longer present.  This prevents undesirable toggling of DAB HMI messages (i.e., metadata) should the DAB signal be intermittent.  Once the timer expires, HMI shall display the DAB Station Not Available message if the current DAB station signal strength does not return to an acceptable receive threshold." Name="DAB_Station_Not_Available" References="GIS-502-4.1.21.6" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_YeMfMd-lEeSfuIbaAz9ajg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
