  <CalDefinition Description="The Explicit_Content_Menu_Item_On calibration defines the default HMI menu state for SXM explicit channel filtering.   When set to (TRUE) explicit content is filtered as determined by the explicit content filter flag in the X65 module. When FALSE, explicit channels are not filtered.  The default state for this calibration is FALSE (Off).  This means all SXM channels shall be shown with no explicit channel filtering.  When TRUE, HMI shall not allow explicit channels to be tuned." Name="Explicit_Content_Menu_Item_On" References="GIS-502 6.1.1.1" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
