  <CalDefinition Description="The HD_Radio_Menu_Item_On determines the HMI menu default state (HD On or HD Off) when HD Radio is activated in the tuner.  If HD Radio is not active in the tuner, the state of this calibration shall be set to FALSE via a cal override.  The default state for this calibration is TRUE (On).  This means the HMI menu item default setting for HD Radio is &quot;ON&quot; and the user can select and listen to HD stations and see the HD icon/metadata in the now playing screen and the station list view.  When set to OFF, HD Radio is disabled and therefore the tuner will not process HD stations.  In addition, the user will not see the HD icon and associated metadata in the now playing screen and the station list view." Name="HD_Radio_Menu_Item_On" References="GIS-502 4.1.28.1" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
